RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUSTIN'S LEGACY tipped inwards early around the first turn and set a controlled pace inside, was roused early around the far turn, opened up from the three path into the lane, and was driven out. LYTE CRUDE had to steady between foes midway around the first turn, chased in the three path, was cued from the four path around the far turn, swung out to the six path into the stretch, and ran on for place. KING D'ORO steadied along the inside into the first turn, tracked inside, was under urging around the far turn, tipped out to the four path into the lane, and kept on for show. JEBY was unhurried along the inside, under coaxing from the rail early around the far turn, shifted out to the five path and was cued left handed into the stretch, but drifted out thru the stretch while bumping an outer foe, and finished evenly. RIGHT KARMA bumped with an inner foe at the start, rated in the four path, was under a drive in the six path entering the stretch, but got herded outward and bumped through the stretch, and could not factor. RIGEL raced up close in the two path, was driven between foes around the far turn, but faded down the lane. IMMENSE FAITH was fractious in the gate, hopped at the start and bumped with an outer foe, trailed in the three path early and made no impact. DELVEY had an awkward start, stalked in the four path but backed up early around the far turn.
